16 court-to-community initiatives such as the Smart Justice video series, an annual youth law
17 camp, and student mentorship programs during her tenure; and
18 WHEREAS, under her leadership, the Magistrate Court of Rockdale County received the
19 2018 Judicial Clearance Rate Excellence Award from the Judicial Council of Georgia
20 Standing Committee on Judicial Workload Assessment; and
21 WHEREAS, Mallory Minor has established a glowing reputation of renown throughout
22 Georgia for her dedication to the legal profession, her commitment to mentoring youth, and
23 her exemplary service on numerous boards and organizations; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
25 extraordinary servant leader be appropriately recognized.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 congratulate and commend Mallory Minor for receiving the 2025 Yellow Rose Nikki T.
28 Randall Servant Leadership Award and extend best wishes for her continued success.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Mallory Minor.
